overview: Numerous well-known biographies are closely linked to the University of Vienna, which is celebrating its 650th anniversary this year. Director Karin Schiller lets successful people from all disciplines look back on their student days in Vienna and thus creates the image of an institution that, even after centuries, still aims at the core of society with the education it imparts.
